  "prompt": "Do all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE?",
  "response": "Not all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE). The availability depends on the device's age and specifications:\n\n1. Newer smartphones (roughly from 2013 onwards) typically include Bluetooth 4.0 or later versions like 4.1, 4.2, 5.0, or 5.1.\n\n2. Older smartphones manufactured before 2013 may have earlier Bluetooth versions (2.0, 3.0) that do not support BLE.\n\n3. As of 2023, most modern smartphones come with Bluetooth 5.0 or 5.1, which include BLE capabilities.\n\nTo confirm your specific device's Bluetooth version, you can:\n- Check the device specifications online\n- Look in your phone's settings menu\n- Contact the manufacturer's customer support\n\nIf you want to know about a particular smartphone model, it's best to check its specific technical specifications.",
